a:r.a:t: NPO Users will access the publicly information available published on the NPO National Registry Portal developed using Angular or a similar technology. NPO Portal users will be authenticated using UAE Pass or Emirates ID to access the NPO related eservices.

Existing SWP platform will be extended for the NPO requirements. NPO requests created through the NPO Portal will land in the Dynamics 365 Requests module. Back-end users will be presented with a guided process that will have different stages and steps as per the process. Users will also be presented with "next best actions" for a step to ensure consistency. Dashboards and reports will be configured using the native capabilities of Dynamics 365.

Dynamics 365 will be integrated with the external systems using the existing Web APIs available through the MoCD ESB. This layer will support three types of integration i.e. near real-time, batch synchronization and on-demand refresh of data from the core applications. The integration approach will ensure that the data is refreshed periodically and end users have access to the latest information of the Customer.
API Based Integrations via MoCD Enterprise Service Bus (ESB)
Core Platform Features (Business Process Management, Plugins, Metadata, API & SDK etc.)
